# Bella Consultancy - WordPress Child Theme

Bella Consultancy is a child theme of the WordPress default theme Twenty Twenty-Four. This child theme is designed specifically for the Bella Consultancy website, with custom styles and functions to meet the unique needs of consultancy and business services.

## Installation

To install the Bella Consultancy theme, you must have the Twenty Twenty-Four parent theme installed on your WordPress site.

1. Download the Bella Consultancy theme from the repository.
2. Navigate to your WordPress dashboard, go to `Appearance > Themes > Add New > Upload Theme`.
3. Choose the downloaded `bella-consultancy.zip` file and click `Install Now`.
4. Once the theme is uploaded, click `Activate` to set Bella Consultancy as the active theme.

Alternatively, you can upload the theme folder directly to your server:

1. Extract the `bella-consultancy.zip` file.
2. Upload the `bella-consultancy` folder to the `wp-content/themes/` directory on your server.
3. Go to `Appearance > Themes` on your WordPress dashboard and activate the Bella Consultancy theme.

## Features

- Inherits all the functionality and design of the Twenty Twenty-Four theme.
- Custom color schemes tailored to the Bella Consultancy brand identity.
- Additional widget areas for consultancy-specific content.
- Custom page templates for displaying services and testimonials.
- Optimized for performance with minimal overhead.

## Customization

Bella Consultancy allows for extensive customization via the WordPress Customizer:

- Navigate to `Appearance > Customize` in your WordPress dashboard.
- Here you can change colors, fonts, layout options, and more.
- Any changes you make will be previewed in real time before saving.

## Development

For developers wishing to extend the theme:

- The theme is located in the `wp-content/themes/bella-consultancy/` folder.
- Enqueue styles and scripts in the `functions.php` file.
- Use WordPress hooks and filters to modify theme functionality.
- Create custom templates by copying them from the parent theme and modifying as needed.

## Support

For support with this theme, please visit the [repo issues](https://github.com/bellaconsultancy/bella-consultancy-wp-theme/issues).

